cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper introduces a new information theoretic formulation called multi-version coding to study storage costs of consistent distributed storage systems. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the application of distributed storage systems to distributed computing and implementation of key-value stores. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with the storage and retrieval of data in distributed storage systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the requirement of consistency in distributed storage systems, which is a key aspect of system design and control. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the implementation of key-value stores, which are commonly used in networking and internet architecture.
